{"comments":"Color Dynamics Atoms — Bounded numeric parameters for color variation.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nColor dynamics atoms represent the bounded numeric primitives for\ncontrolling how brush color varies during a stroke. Each jitter parameter\nspecifies a percentage of maximum variation, with deterministic bounds.\n\n## HSB Jitter Model\n\nColor variation operates in HSB (Hue, Saturation, Brightness) space:\n\n- **Hue Jitter**: ±180° around the color wheel at 100%\n- **Saturation Jitter**: 0% to base saturation at 100%\n- **Brightness Jitter**: 0% to base brightness at 100%\n\nThis model matches traditional painting software behavior and provides\nintuitive control over color variation.\n\n## Foreground/Background Position\n\nWhen source is ForegroundBackground, a position value (0-1) determines\nthe interpolation between the two colors. This can be controlled by\npressure, tilt, velocity, or stroke distance.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n- Schema.Bounded\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[152,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[152,19]},"title":"HueJitter"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","ColorDynamics","Atoms"],"HueJitter"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[154,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[154,1]},"title":"eqHueJitter"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","ColorDynamics","Atoms"],"HueJitter"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[155,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[155,1]},"title":"ordHueJitter"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","ColorDynamics","Atoms"],"HueJitter"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[158,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[157,1]},"title":"showHueJitter"}],"comments":"Hue jitter percentage (0-100).\n\nRandom variation in hue per dab. At 100%, hue varies ±180° around\nthe color wheel (all colors possible). At 50%, ±90°. At 0%, no variation.\n\nThis is percentage of maximum variation, not degrees.\nClamps to bounds.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[152,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[152,1]},"title":"HueJitter"},{"children":[],"comments":"Smart constructor that clamps to bounds.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","ColorDynamics","Atoms"],"HueJitter"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[165,33],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Atoms.purs","start":[165,1]},"title":"hueJitter"},{"children":[],"comments":"Bounds for HueJitter: 0 to 100, clamps.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"NumberBounds"],"tag":"T